# Switch Toast to Sonner

## Current State
- Custom React Aria toast using `UNSTABLE_Toast` API (~350 lines)
- Located at `packages/ui/src/components/ui/toast/toast.tsx`
- Sonner v2.0.7 already installed but unused

## Target State
- Simple Sonner wrapper (~30 lines) matching taki-ui pattern
- Same external API: `toast.success()`, `toast.error()`, etc.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Create Sonner wrapper
```tsx
// packages/ui/src/components/ui/sonner/sonner.tsx
'use client';

import { useTheme } from 'next-themes'; // or custom theme hook
import { Toaster as SonnerToaster, toast } from 'sonner';
import type { ToasterProps } from 'sonner';

function Toaster(props: ToasterProps) {
  const { theme = 'system' } = useTheme?.() ?? {};

  return (
    <SonnerToaster
      className="toaster group"
      theme={theme as ToasterProps['theme']}
      toastOptions={{
        classNames: {
          actionButton: 'group-[.toast]:bg-primary group-[.toast]:text-primary-foreground',
          cancelButton: 'group-[.toast]:bg-muted group-[.toast]:text-muted-foreground',
          description: 'group-[.toast]:text-muted-foreground',
          toast: 'group toast group-[.toaster]:bg-background group-[.toaster]:text-foreground group-[.toaster]:border-border group-[.toaster]:shadow-lg',
        },
      }}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}

export { Toaster, toast };
```

### 2. Update exports
- Create `packages/ui/src/components/ui/sonner/index.ts`
- Update `packages/ui/src/index.ts` to export from sonner instead of toast
- Keep backward-compatible exports if needed

### 3. Update/Remove old toast
- Delete or archive `packages/ui/src/components/ui/toast/toast.tsx`
- Update stories to use Sonner API

### 4. Update stories
```tsx
// sonner.stories.tsx
import { toast, Toaster } from './sonner';

// API is similar:
toast.success('Saved!');
toast.error('Failed');
toast('Message', { description: 'Details' });
toast('With action', {
  action: { label: 'Undo', onClick: () => {} },
});
```

## API Comparison

| Feature | Current | Sonner |
|---------|---------|--------|
| Basic | `toast('msg')` | `toast('msg')` |
| Success | `toast.success('msg')` | `toast.success('msg')` |
| Error | `toast.error('msg')` | `toast.error('msg')` |
| Loading | `toast.loading('msg')` | `toast.loading('msg')` |
| Promise | `toast.promise(p, {...})` | `toast.promise(p, {...})` |
| Dismiss | `toast.dismiss(id)` | `toast.dismiss(id)` |
| With desc | `toast({ title, description })` | `toast('title', { description })` |
| With action | `toast({ title, action: {...} })` | `toast('title', { action: {...} })` |

## Breaking Changes
- `toast({ title: 'x', description: 'y' })` → `toast('x', { description: 'y' })`
- Action format stays same

## Files to Modify
1. Create: `packages/ui/src/components/ui/sonner/sonner.tsx`
2. Create: `packages/ui/src/components/ui/sonner/index.ts`
3. Delete: `packages/ui/src/components/ui/toast/` directory
4. Update: `packages/ui/src/index.ts` (change toast → sonner export)

## Dependencies
- sonner v2.0.7 (already installed)
- May need theme hook from app (next-themes or custom)

# Extract Shared dropdownItemStyles

## Current State
- Menu item styles duplicated across multiple components
- Each component defines its own item styling
- Inconsistencies possible between DropdownMenu, ContextMenu, Select, Combobox, etc.

## Target State
- Single `dropdownItemStyles` tv utility shared across all menu-like components
- Consistent hover, focus, selected, and disabled states
- Easy to update all menus at once

## Reference: taki-ui pattern

```tsx
// From taki-ui list-box.tsx
export const dropdownItemStyles = tv({
  extend: focusRing,
  base: [
    'group flex cursor-default items-center gap-2 rounded-sm px-2 py-1.5',
    'text-sm outline-0 select-none',
  ],
  variants: {
    isDisabled: {
      true: 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none',
    },
    isFocused: {
      true: 'bg-accent text-accent-foreground',
    },
    isSelected: {
      true: 'font-medium',
    },
    variant: {
      default: '',
      destructive: 'text-destructive focus:bg-destructive/10 focus:text-destructive',
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: {
    variant: 'default',
  },
});
```

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Create shared styles file

```tsx
// packages/ui/src/lib/dropdown-styles.ts
import { tv } from 'tailwind-variants';
import { focusRing } from './focus-ring';

export const dropdownItemStyles = tv({
  extend: focusRing,
  base: [
    'group/dropdown-item relative flex cursor-default items-center gap-2',
    'rounded-sm px-2 py-1.5 text-sm outline-none select-none',
    // Icon sizing
    "[&_svg:not([class*='size-'])]:size-4 [&_svg]:pointer-events-none [&_svg]:shrink-0",
  ],
  variants: {
    isDisabled: {
      true: 'pointer-events-none opacity-50',
    },
    isFocused: {
      true: 'bg-accent text-accent-foreground',
    },
    isSelected: {
      true: 'font-semibold',
    },
    variant: {
      default: '',
      destructive: [
        'text-destructive',
        'data-[focused]:bg-destructive/10 data-[focused]:text-destructive',
      ],
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: {
    variant: 'default',
  },
});

// For menu content containers
export const dropdownContentStyles = tv({
  base: [
    'z-50 min-w-[8rem] overflow-hidden rounded-md border bg-popover p-1',
    'text-popover-foreground shadow-md',
    // Animations
    'data-[state=open]:animate-in data-[state=closed]:animate-out',
    'data-[state=closed]:fade-out-0 data-[state=open]:fade-in-0',
    'data-[state=closed]:zoom-out-95 data-[state=open]:zoom-in-95',
    'data-[side=bottom]:slide-in-from-top-2 data-[side=left]:slide-in-from-right-2',
    'data-[side=right]:slide-in-from-left-2 data-[side=top]:slide-in-from-bottom-2',
  ],
});

// For separators
export const dropdownSeparatorStyles = 'bg-muted -mx-1 my-1 h-px';

// For labels/headers
export const dropdownLabelStyles = 'px-2 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-muted-foreground';
```

### Step 2: Update components to use shared styles

**Components to update:**
- [ ] DropdownMenu - `dropdown-menu.tsx`
- [ ] ContextMenu - `context-menu.tsx`
- [ ] Select (items) - `select.tsx`
- [ ] Combobox (items) - `combobox.tsx`
- [ ] Command (items) - `command.tsx`
- [ ] Menubar (items) - `menubar.tsx`

### Step 3: Example usage

```tsx
// dropdown-menu.tsx
import { dropdownItemStyles, dropdownContentStyles } from '../../../lib/dropdown-styles';

function DropdownMenuItem({ className, variant, ...props }) {
  return (
    <DropdownMenuPrimitive.Item
      className={cx(
        (renderProps) => dropdownItemStyles({ ...renderProps, variant }),
        className,
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}

function DropdownMenuContent({ className, ...props }) {
  return (
    <DropdownMenuPrimitive.Content
      className={cn(dropdownContentStyles(), className)}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}
```

## Components Analysis

| Component | Item Component | Content Component | Notes |
|-----------|---------------|-------------------|-------|
| DropdownMenu | DropdownMenuItem | DropdownMenuContent | Primary target |
| ContextMenu | ContextMenuItem | ContextMenuContent | Same structure |
| Select | SelectItem | SelectContent | RAC based |
| Combobox | ComboboxItem | ComboboxContent | RAC based |
| Command | CommandItem | CommandList | cmdk based |
| Menubar | MenubarItem | MenubarContent | Radix based |

## Files to Create/Modify

1. Create: `packages/ui/src/lib/dropdown-styles.ts`
2. Update: `packages/ui/src/lib/utils.ts` (re-export)
3. Update: dropdown-menu.tsx
4. Update: context-menu.tsx
5. Update: select.tsx
6. Update: combobox.tsx
7. Update: command.tsx
8. Update: menubar.tsx

